ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='I see that `packages/design-system/widgetbook/main.dart` has a lot mo
re content than `packages/design-system/lib/widgetbook/main.dart`. The one in `l
ib/widgetbook/` seems to be the correct one based on the design system structure
(since the package exports from `lib/`). The duplicate at `packages/design-syste
m/widgetbook/main.dart` seems like an old or misplaced file. Let me check if it\
's tracked.\n\nActually, looking at the diff output, the file at `packages/desig
n-system/widgetbook/main.dart` contains extra demo widgets for DevTools that are
NOT in `lib/widgetbook/main.dart`. This is suspicious - it looks like the PR may
have incorrectly placed the widgetbook content.\n\nWait, looking at the PR file 
list again:\n```\npackages/design-system/lib/widgetbook/main.dart\npackages/desi
gn-system/widgetbook/main.dart\n```\n\nBoth are in the PR. The `lib/widgetbook/m
ain.dart` is the one actually imported/used by the package. The `widgetbook/main
.dart` at the package root is a duplicate that\'s likely never used. This is a s
tructural issue.\n\nNow let me also check a few more things:\n1. The `pubspec.ya
ml` for the design system package\n2. Whether the `matching.yaml` API contract i
ncludes `super_like` but the mobile only has `like`/`pass` buttons\n3. Whether t
he `api.md` docs say `POST /match_actions` but the actual code uses `POST /match
ing/actions`\n\nWait, looking at `api.md` line 19: "POST /api/v1/match_actions" 
but the actual controller uses `@Controller("matching")` and `@Post("actions")`,
so the URL is `/api/v1/matching/actions`. The docs/api/matching.md correctly say
s `/matching/actions`.\n\nBut `api.md` in design-docs says:\n| POST | 创建 | `PO
ST /api/v1/match_actions` |\n\nThis is a general API design doc that may be outd
ated or just an example. Since the PR doesn\'t modify `docs/design-docs/api.md`,
this isn\'t a new issue introduced by this PR.\n\nLet me think about what are th
e most important issues to flag:\n\n## Blocking Issues\n1. **`last_active_at` fi
eld is never updated** - The migration adds it, the scoring query uses it, but n
o code ever writes to it. This makes the "recently active" scoring completely br
oken.\n2. **`city` mode doesn\'t filter by city boundary** - It uses 50km same a
s `nearby`. PRD specifies "同城市，根据用户当前位置行政边界".\n3. **`packages/de
sign-system/widgetbook/main.dart` is a duplicate/misplaced file** - This creates
confusion and maintenance burden. The actual widgetbook is at `lib/widgetbook/ma
in.dart`.\n\nWait, is the duplicate file really blocking? It\'s more of a mainte
nance issue. Let me reconsider.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at the `city
` mode issue - the PRD says:\n> `mode` 参数：`nearby`（默认 50km）、`city`（同城
市，根据用户当前位置行政边界）、`nationwide`（全国）。\n\nThe current implementa
tion treats `city` as 50km. This is a functional deviation from the PRD. Users s
electing "city" mode won\'t actually get city-filtered results. However, impleme
nting actual city boundary filtering requires geocoding/reverse geocoding which 
is complex. Is this truly blocking, or is it a known gap?\n\nGiven the PRD expli
citly states this as a requirement, and the current implementation silently give
s wrong results (users think they\'re seeing city-only results but they\'re seei
ng 50km radius), I\'d mark this as Major, not Blocking, because the feature stil
l "works" (returns results), just with incorrect filtering.\n\n## Major Issues\n
1. **`last_active_at` never updated** - Actually, I think this IS blocking becau
se it breaks a core scoring feature. But wait - is there any existing code that 
should update it? The PR doesn\'t add the update mechanism. According to the PRD
, this field is used for scoring. Without writes, the scoring will always give 0
.1 weight (the ELSE branch) for all users. This is a significant functional defe
ct. But the PR is about "matching module", not the "activity tracking module". M
aybe updating `last_active_at` is someone else\'s responsibility (e.g., auth log
in updates `last_login_at`, profile module might update `last_active_at`). Howev
er, since this PR introduces the field and depends on it for scoring, it should 
at minimum document that updates are needed, or ideally implement it. I\'ll mark
this as Major because the field was added in this PR specifically for matching s
coring.\n\nActually wait, let me re-read the PRD requirements more carefully:\n>
近期活跃用户优先（权重 30%）：根据 `last_active_at` 分档（24h 内 1.0，7 天内 0.7
，30 天内 0.4，其余 0.1）。\n\nIf `last_active_at` is null for all users, the CA
SE statement falls to ELSE (0.1). So the scoring still works, just without the r
ecency bonus. This means the feature is degraded but not completely broken. I\'l
l mark it as Major.\n\n2. **HomePage uses private `_CardStackArea` instead of `S
wipeCardStack`** - This is code duplication and violates the design system appro
ach. Major.\n3. **`ExternalMatchReceived` doesn\'t preserve previous state** - W
hen a match is received via socket, the dialog dismiss will incorrectly show emp
ty state. Major.\n4. **Duplicate widgetbook file** - `packages/design-system/wid
getbook/main.dart` should not exist if `lib/widgetbook/main.dart` is the actual 
one.\n5. **`ProfileCompletionGuard` returns wrong error code** - Returns 1000 in
stead of 1001 for incomplete profile.\n6. **No Design-Only PR visual artifacts**
- Missing golden file tests or widgetbook screenshots.\n\nLet me check one more 
thing about the `_CardStackArea` - the HomePage doesn\'t use `SwipeCardStack` at
all! It has its own `_CardStackArea` with identical logic. The design-spec says 
"卡片堆叠容器，管理多层卡片渲染与手势冲突" and lists `SwipeCardStack` as the com
ponent. The fact that HomePage duplicates this logic is a clear architectural is
sue.\n\nAlso, I noticed that `SwipeCardStack` is in the design-system but is nev
er actually used in the app! It\'s only in widgetbook. The actual app uses `_Car
dStackArea` in HomePage. That\'s a major issue.\n\nWait, looking at `HomePage` m
ore carefully:\n```dart\nclass _CardStackArea extends StatefulWidget {\n  final 
List<Map<String, dynamic>> cards;\n  final Function(int index, String direction)
? onSwipe;\n  final VoidCallback? onEnd;\n```\n\nThis is almost identical to `Sw
ipeCardStack`. The duplication is clear.\n\nAlso, I want to check if there\'s an
issue with the `SwipeActionRequest.toJson()` method:\n```dart\nMap<String, dynam
ic> toJson() {\n  final json = <String, dynamic>{};\n    json[r\'target_id\'] = 
this.targetId;\n    json[r\'action\'] = this.action;\n  return json;\n}\n```\n\n
Wait, `this.action` is a `SwipeActionRequestActionEnum`, not a String. When pass
ed to Dio as POST body, will it serialize correctly? The `toJson()` returns `thi
s.action` directly, but `SwipeActionRequestActionEnum` has a `toJson()` method t
hat returns String. However, Dart\'s `Map<String, dynamic>` won\'t automatically
call `toJson()` on nested objects. When Dio serializes this Map to JSON, it will
call `jsonEncode`, which will try to encode `SwipeActionRequestActionEnum` - sin
ce it doesn\'t have a custom JSON encoder, it might call `toString()` or fail.\n
\nActually, looking at the generated code more carefully:\n```dart\njson[r\'acti
